header.gameNote: HOOPS FOR HOPE CLASSIC AT PUERTO VALLARTA MEXICO

article.headline: Rider 74, Milwaukee 60
article.story: PUERTO VALLARTA, Mexico -- Anthony Myles scored 14 points as Rider beat Milwaukee 74-60 on Sunday in the Hoops for Hope Classic. Myles and Daniel Stewart, who had 11 points, had six rebounds apiece for the Broncos (4-3). Junior Fortunat added 11 points. After being tied very early in the first half, Rider led 43-31 at halftime, with Nurideen Lindsey leading the fight with nine points. Milwaukee scored first in the second half off a layup by Demetrius Harris, but the Panthers could not get close in the half. Rider shot 45 percent from the field for the game, keeping the lead. Milwaukee (2-4) shot just 37.5 percent from the field. Evan Richard scored 11 for the Panthers. Harris and Austin Arians each had 10 points. Thiemo Niang led with five rebounds and six assists.
